%N A387883 a(n) is the number of regions into which the plane is divided by n^2 circles of radius 1, the centers of which are located at the nodes of a square lattice n X n.
%C A387883 These n^2 circles, intersecting, divide the plane into parts, among which there are equal ones: 1st group - 4 parts, 2nd group - 4*(n - 1) parts, 3rd group - 4*(n - 2) parts, 4th group - (n - 1)^2 parts, 5th group - 2*(n - 1)*(n - 2) parts, 6th group - 4*(n - 1)^2 parts and 1 external part. See the link to the illustration.
%H A387883 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A387883/b387883.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%H A387883 Nicolay Avilov, <a href="/A387883/a387883.jpg">Illustration of the first five terms</a>.
%H A387883 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,-3,1).
%F A387883 a(n) = 7*n^2 - 8*n + 2, for n > 1.
%F A387883 From _Stefano Spezia_, Sep 11 2025: (Start)
%F A387883 G.f.: (1 - x + 11*x^2 + 4*x^3 - x^4)/(1 - x)^3.
%F A387883 E.g.f.: exp(x)*(2 - x + 7*x^2) - 1 + x. (End)
%e A387883 a(1) = 2, because one circle divides the plane into 2 parts;
%e A387883 a(2) = 14, because four circles divide the plane into 14 parts;
%e A387883 a(5) = 4 + 4*4 +4*3 + 4^2 + 2*4*3 + 4*4^2 + 1 = 137, see the link;
%e A387883 a(6) = 7*6^2 - 8*6 + 2 = 206.
%t A387883 A387883[n_] := If[n < 2, n + 1, n*(7*n - 8) + 2]; Array[A387883, 100, 0] (* or *)
